<TITLE> Brazil squad for World Cup qualifiers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 RIO DE JANEIRO, March 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Brazil have named the following squad for their World Cup qualifiers away to Ecuador on March 29 and at home to Peru on April 1: Goalkeepers: Julio Cesar (Inter Milan), Doni (AS Roma) Defenders: Daniel Alves (Barcelona), Maicon (Inter Milan), Lucio (Bayern Munich), Miranda (Sao Paulo), Thiago Silva (AC Milan), Luisao (Benfica), Marcelo (Real Madrid), Kleber (Internacional) Midfielders: Gilberto Silva (Panathinaikos), Josue (VfL Wolfsburg), Anderson (Manchester United), Felipe Melo (Fiorentina), Elano (Manchester City), Julio Baptista (AS Roma), Kaka (AC Milan) Forwards: Ronaldinho (AC Milan), Alexandre Pato (AC Milan), Luis Fabiano (Sevilla), Adriano (Inter Milan), Robinho (Manchester City)
